# Git Workflow

## Branch Policy

**NEVER commit directly to `main`.** All work happens on feature branches.

### Branch Naming

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Article | `article/{slug}` | `article/vybir-nythky-polotna` |
| Feature | `feat/{short-description}` | `feat/add-articles-index` |
| Bug fix | `fix/{short-description}` | `fix/og-image-path` |
| Design/UI | `style/{short-description}` | `style/hero-layout` |
| Docs | `docs/{short-description}` | `docs/update-agents` |
| Refactor | `refactor/{short-description}` | `refactor/base-layout` |
| CI/CD | `ci/{short-description}` | `ci/cache-npm` |

Use lowercase, hyphens. Keep names short (2–4 words).

### Before Starting Work

1. `git branch --show-current`
2. If on **`main`** — create a branch before changing files
3. `git pull origin main`
4. `git checkout -b {type}/{description}`

## Conventional Commits

Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/).

### Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>
```

### Types

| Type | When |
|---|---|
| `feat` | New feature or new article |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `style` | CSS/design (no logic change) |
| `refactor` | Restructure without feature/fix |
| `perf` | Performance |
| `test` | Tests |
| `ci` | CI/CD (e.g. deploy.yml) |
| `chore` | Maintenance, deps |
| `content` | Article edits (not new article) |

### Scopes (examples)

`article`, `ui`, `layout`, `seo`, `config`, `deps`, `skill`, `rule`

### Rules

- Lowercase imperative verb after the colon; max ~72 chars on first line
- No trailing period on the subject line

Use the **conventional-commits** skill for commits and PRs to **AZANIR/Gapta**, base **`main`**.
